# The MCM translation tables are UTF-16LE (with a BOM and CRLF line endings).
# Marking them `binary` (= -text -diff) guarantees Git never applies line-ending
# conversion to them, which would corrupt the 2-byte encoding. Git already
# auto-detects them as binary via their null bytes; this pins that behavior so a
# checkout on any platform or Git version can't mangle them.
interface/translations/*.txt binary
